In the course of the social security law the following subjects will be dealt with: the system of social security, general principles of social security and European social security, the two fields of social security, social insurance and social assistance, different social benefits and its legal regulation in Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general purpose of the course is to teach the theoretical basic knowledge of the social security law, to explain the development of the principles and main institutions of the social security law and the connections between main institutes of social security law; to give the deep knowledge about the legal regulation of the social protection and about the system of social security in Estonia and its legal regulation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course the students are able to: - explain the nature of the main institutes of the social security law and nature of the general principles and relations between them;  - understand the different branches of the social security law and the specific aspects of their application; - to apply the norms and rules of social security law in case of solving the social security disputes ( to produce a well-structured legal opinion of a case); - use the case law and the legal literature by solving the cases in social security law; - apply different methods of interpretation in order to explain the content and the aim of different social security norms;
